==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adios
<hw>A`dios"</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧`dy⟦osl⟧s")</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos>
<ety>[Sp., fr. L. <ets>ad</ets> to + <ets>deus</ets> god. Cf.
<er>Adieu</er>.]</ety> <def>Adieu; farewell; good-by; -- chiefly used
among Spanish-speaking people; <as>as, <ex>adios</ex> amigos
(<sig>good-bye friends</sig>)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is often pronounced
<pr>⟦adot⟧*d⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧s</pr>, but the Spanish accent, though weak, is
on the final syllable.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adipescent</ent>⟦br⟧
